# Visual Confirmation Required — MANDATORY

## Nothing is complete until you see it working with your own eyes

Every change that affects what users see MUST be visually confirmed before marking it done. Screenshots or screen recordings are required evidence. "The build passes" is not confirmation. "curl returns 200" is not confirmation. You must SEE the rendered page.

## When visual confirmation is required

- Any change to a page, component, layout, or style
- Any change to data fetching that affects what renders
- Any fix for a reported UI issue
- Any performance improvement (show before/after metrics)
- Any new feature, section, or page
- Any change to navigation, links, or routing

## When it is NOT required

- Documentation-only changes (markdown files, comments)
- Test file changes (unit tests, e2e test specs)
- Config changes that don't affect rendering (tsconfig, eslint config)
- Script-only changes (standalone scripts not part of the app)

## How to confirm visually

### Option 1: Playwright screenshots (preferred for speed)
```bash
npx playwright screenshot --browser chromium "http://localhost:PORT/page" /opt/cursor/artifacts/screenshots/descriptive-name.png --viewport-size 1400,900 --timeout 30000
```
Take screenshots at both desktop (1400x900) and mobile (390x844) if the change is responsive.

### Option 2: Screen recording
Use `RecordScreen` to capture a walkthrough of the feature/fix.

### Option 3: Browser console check
```bash
node -e "const { chromium } = require('playwright'); ..." 
```
Capture console errors and verify no JavaScript failures.

## What to verify in screenshots

1. **The content renders** — not a blank page, not an error boundary, not a skeleton
2. **Real data shows** — not placeholder text, not zeros, not "Coming soon"
3. **Images/photos load** — not broken image icons
4. **Layout is correct** — no overlapping elements, no cut-off text, no misalignment
5. **Mobile is responsive** — content stacks properly, no horizontal scroll
6. **No console errors** — no JavaScript failures that break hydration

## Evidence must be included

When presenting work to the user:
- Include screenshot artifacts inline in the response
- Reference specific screenshots as proof
- If something doesn't look right, fix it BEFORE presenting

## Integration with other rules

This rule works WITH (not instead of) these existing rules:
- `definition-of-done.mdc` — visual confirmation is part of "done"
- `pre-commit-verification.mdc` — visual check before commit
- `continuous-ui-audit-loop.mdc` — visual audit is ongoing
- `complete-scope-and-best-practices.mdc` — visual quality is part of best practices
- `always-execute.mdc` — take screenshots proactively, don't ask

## Never

- Say "I verified the page loads" without a screenshot to prove it
- Present a fix without showing the before/after
- Mark UI work complete without visual evidence
- Skip mobile screenshots for responsive changes
- Assume a page renders correctly because the build passes
- Trust curl output as visual confirmation — curl shows HTML, not what users see